      "writtenOn": "2018-02-14T17:13:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Initially, I had centralized all allocation \u0026 deletion of the atlas text blob memory in GrTextBlobCache and had a separate tracker variable for the non-memory-pool memory. Unfortunately, the GrTextBlobCache isn\u0027t around when the atlas text blobs are freed in the DDL world (i.e., later and in a different SkSurface).\n\nIt is true that we hope (in the future) to be able to report the VRAM usage of a given DDL at which point we would have a separate memory tracking object with the same lifetime as the DDL. At that point I think would make sense to add that to the GrTextBlobCache and have the GrTextBlobCache and the GrAtlasTextBlob report in. However, even in that world, I don\u0027t know what the client would do if a given DDL is chewing up a lot of RAM. They need to render it and they have to go through a GrAtlasTextBlob to get there.",
